        "title": "docs: clarify OpenClaw vs Codex code mode",
        "body": "Closes #83390\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n- Readers were unclear how OpenClaw native code mode differs from Codex Code Mode. The docs also claimed Codex Code Mode is a \"stable Codex harness surface\", contradicting upstream Codex `Stage::UnderDevelopment`.\n- Fix: Add side-by-side comparison table in `docs/reference/code-mode.md`, cross-link from `docs/plugins/codex-harness.md`. Correct all stability claims on touched pages.\n- Docs only. No runtime, config, or provider changes.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**`docs:list` — all 3 changed pages render correctly:**\n```\n$ node scripts/docs-list.js | grep -E \"code-mode|codex-harness|tool-search\"\nplugins/codex-harness.md - Run OpenClaw embedded agent turns through the bundled Codex app-server harness\nreference/code-mode.md - OpenClaw code mode: an opt-in exec/wait tool surface backed by QuickJS-WASI\n  Read when: ... You need to explain why code mode is different from Codex Code mode ...\ntools/tool-search.md - Tool Search: compact large OpenClaw tool catalogs\n```\n\n**`docs-link-audit` — no broken links:**\n```\n$ node scripts/docs-link-audit.mjs\nbroken_links=0\n```\n\n**Before (main — stale \"stable\" claim):**\n```\n$ git show origin/main:docs/reference/code-mode.md | grep -i \"stable\"\nCodex Code Mode and Codex-native dynamic tool search are stable Codex harness\n```\n**After (fix):** \"upstream Codex marks as under development (`Stage::UnderDevelopment`)\"",
